<div class='slide'>
    <h1>I only want to run this code if....</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>As you have been writing algorithms, you may well have wanted to only perform a particular action <b>if</b> a particular condition is true or false</li>
        <li>If there's no more space on my grid, stop drawing lines</li>
        <li>If the length of my line is more than the size of the gap between lines, execute some instructions</li>
        <li>In Python (as with many other languages), you can use an if statement to do this</li> 
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
    <h1>if / elif / else</h1>
    <ul>
        <li><pre>if condition:
            statement</pre></li>
        <li>You can have zero or more elif statements after an if</li>
        <li>if (and elif) statements can also have an optional else</li>
        <li><a target='new' href='py-html/if-eg.htm'>Example</a> </li>
